@NODE "What is it?"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Description @{fg text}@{bg back}

Koala DataType is a picture datatype for displaying Commodore 64 KoalaPainter images under AmigaOS 3.0 or higher.

KoalaPainter is a very popular C64 graphics image format. @{" Are you nostalgic? " link "Docs/C64_Koala_Painter.ilbm/main"}
Common file name extensions, when present, can be: ".kla", ".koa", ".prg".
Files are 10003 bytes long.

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Requirements @{fg text}@{bg back}

AmigaOS 3.0 or higher running on Motorola 680x0 based computers.
Alternatively an Amiga emulation package is required (Cloanto Amiga Forever recommended).

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Usage @{fg text}@{bg back}

You can use MultiView, or any other image viewers that support datatypes (Visage is my favourite one),
to view Koala images on your Amiga.
If you use MultiView a Workbench screen with 256 colours (8 bit) or more is required.
You can even use programs like Personal Paint to edit one.

I have included a lot of Koala images in the "Images" directory.

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Features @{fg text}@{bg back}

* Resolution of rendered images is 320 x 200 pixels - 16 colours
* C64 colours palette preserved with high accuracy @{" C64 RGB palette " link "Docs/C64_palette.ilbm/main"}
* AmigaGuide documentation including
    * C64 KoalaPainter file format specification
    * a C64 palettes gallery
    * a lot of related and interesting web links
    * a comfortable images browser
* Source code supplied
* More than 40 sample Koala images supplied

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Used platforms @{fg text}@{bg back}

Developed and tested on:
* Cloanto Amiga Forever 2006 Premium Edition, WinUAE 1.2.0, JIT, TCP/IP
* Some AmigaOS 3.9 and AmigaOS 3.5 files, ROM 3.1
* Kickstart 45.57, Workbench 45.3 (12/07/2001)
* System: 68020 68881 (INST: Cache)
* SAS/C Amiga Compiler 6.58 Copyright (c) 1988-1995 SAS Institute Inc.
* dtmake 1.0 a package for DataTypes developers
* 1024 x 768 Workbench screen with 65536 colours (16 bit)
* picture.datatype 45.17 (03/19/2002)

Even tested on:
* A4000
* AmigaOS 3.0, ROM 3.0
* Kickstart 39.106, Workbench 39.29 (09/02/92)
* System: 68030 68882 (INST: Cache Burst) (DATA: Cache NoBurst)
* picture.datatype 39.14 (08/26/1992)

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Source code @{fg text}@{bg back}

Project files are located in the "Source" directory,
they define the picture sub-class and are needed to create the "koala.datatype" file:
* koala_rev.h
* koalapalette.h
* class_iprotos.h
* classbase.h
* classbase.c
* dispatch.c
* koala_rev.i
* classbase.i
* classinit.asm
* endcode.asm
* koala_rev.rev
* smakefile

The DataType Descriptor Function source code for recognition was not available
from the package I used to create the "Koala" DataType Descriptor file.

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Future improvements @{fg text}@{bg back}

* Customized own recognition
* Faster rendition
* Your suggestions

@ENDNODE



@NODE "How to install it on your system"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} Installation @{fg text}@{bg back}

Below are the instructions for doing the installation by hand.

1) Copy the file "Classes/DataTypes/koala.datatype" to the directory "SYS:Classes/DataTypes/".

2) Copy the file "Devs/DataTypes/Koala" and its ".info" file to the directory "SYS:Devs/DataTypes/".

3) Activate the Koala DataType by
     * double-clicking its icon or
     * by executing the Shell command "AddDataTypes SYS:Devs/DataTypes/koala.datatype REFRESH" or
     * by rebooting your Amiga.

@ENDNODE



