@NODE "C64 KoalaPainter file format"

@{bg fill}@{fg shine} C64 KoalaPainter file format @{fg text}@{bg back}

As a multicolour-format these images consist of a bitmap, a videoram and a colourram.
The resolution is 160 x 200 pixels - 16 colours. One pixel represents an area 2 * 1 pixels big.
The screen is divided into 40 * 25 attribute squares. Each attribute square is 4 * 8 pixels big.
Each pixel is defined by 2 bits and can have one of 4 different colours
  * background / foreground colour from videoram for its square
  * screencolour for its square
  * background colour (the same for the whole picture).
So there is a maximum of 4 colours per attribute square out of the total 16 colours.

Structure:
Offset   Length   Contents
$0000    $1F40    Bitmap
$1F40    $03E8    Screen-RAM
$2328    $03E8    Colour-RAM
$2710    $0001    Background colour (1)
(1) High nibble is set to 0.

This is where the 4 colours come from:
%00 from the background colour at $D021
%01 from the high nibble of the movable colour-ram
%10 from the low nibble of the movable colour-ram
%11 from the low nibble of the normal colour-ram at $D800

Search on Internet for more details.

@ENDNODE



